Fudbalski klub Mladost Luani (Serbian Cyrillic:   Maoc a) is a football club based in Luani, Serbia. They played in the Serbian Superliga, the top division of Serbian football. They were the champions for the 2006-2007 season in Serbian First League and have been promoted to the Serbian Superliga. Mladost was playing in the Second Division of Serbia for five seasons before being promoted to the elite division. The team is known for its fierce rivalry with FK Borac aak and its supporters, the Uranium Boys. Serbian First League: As of April 2012. Note: Flags indicate national team as has been defined under FIFA eligibility rules. Players may hold more than one non-FIFA nationality. The stadium of FK Mladost Luani holds 8,000 people. Players with national team appearances:[1] For the list of all current and former players with Wikipedia article, please see Category:FK Mladost Luani players. 
